Sequence Information.Family: Belongs to the frog skin active peptide family (Brevinin subfamily)
Sequence Information.Target Organism: [Ref.21871946]Gram-positive bacteria:Staphylococcus aureus (MIC=14.4 µM), Bacillus cereus (MIC=14.4 µM), Streptococcus lactis (MIC=14.4 µM);Gram-negative bacterium:Escherichia coli (MIC>100 µM).
Sequence Information.Cytotoxicity: No cytotoxicity information found in the reference(s) presented
Sequence Information.Function: Temporin-1CEa exhibits the greatest ability to inhibit the growth of MCF-7 cells. Also temporin-1CEa shows hemolytic effect to human erythrocytes and has no significant cytotoxicity to normal HUVSMCs at concentrations showed potent antitumor activity.

Literature.Title: Antitumor effects and cell selectivity of temporin-1CEa, an antimicrobial peptide from the skin secretions of the Chinese brown frog (Rana chensinensis).
Literature.Author: Wang C, Li HB, Li S, Tian LL, Shang DJ.

Literature.Title: Molecular cloning of cDNAs encoding antimicrobial peptide precursors from the skin of the Chinese brown frog, Rana chensinensis.
